Article.ArticleTitle: [Study on the effect and its mechanisms of 5F from Pteri semipinnata L. on the cell cycle of highly metastatic ovarian carcinoma HO-8910PM cells].

AbstractText: To study the effect and its possible mechanism of 5F from Pteri semipinnata L on the cell cycle of human highly metastatic ovarian carcinoma HO-8910PM cells.

MTT assay was used to examine the effect of 5F on proliferation of HO-8910PM cells after 24 hours treatment; The cell cycle was assessed by flow cytometry (FCM); The expression level of NF-kappaB (p65) FAK and the level of phosphorylated FAK were assessed by Western blot analysis.

5F from Pteris semipinnata L. could inhibit the proliferation of HO-8910PM cell and block the cell cycle at G2/M phase. The expression level of NF-kappaB (P65) protein decreased obviously in HO-8910PM cells treated with 25 - 100 micromol/L 5F for 24 hours, and the effect appeared in a dose-dependent manner. 5F up-regulated significantly the expression of FAK, down-regulated the level of phosphorylated FAK.
The effect on cell cycle of 5F from Pteri semipinnata L is involved in the expression of NF-kappaF(p65), FAK and the level of phosphorylated FAK.
